  "language": "en",
  "text": "Excuse me sir, how old were you when you became a millionaire? Probably around 22. So you made it young. I was very fortunate and blessed. It won a lot of business for you it man, how did you get rich that early? I was fortunate to be a quarterback in the NFL. So what's your name? My name's Tim Tebow. Man I go all over the world interviewing millionaires and billionaires to help the younger generation. Can I get a minute with you for the channel? Yeah of course. What was the most amount of money that you made in a single year? Somewhere between like 5 and 10 million or something I can't even remember, yeah. What is the greatest piece of advice that you've received throughout your career? The greatest form of tragedy is being successful at everything that doesn't matter. But we can take that success and we can use it for things that really matter. Now for the people watching, a lot of them know you as an NFL player, but after your career you're doing something right now that nobody else is doing. What are you doing right now? We're trying to fight back against the greatest evils in the world and that is human trafficking, child exploitation, and child sacrifice. How crazy is that for people that don't understand the magnitude? Today there's 50 plus million people that are being trafficked right now. People have no idea. We have no idea. We're truly so many times we really do have no idea, but we have to be able to spread that awareness and it's taking place in every community in our country. Do you believe in God? I do. Who is your God? My God is the God of the Bible, God the Father, God the Son, and God the Holy Spirit. So you believe in Jesus? I do. You're not afraid to say that either? No I'm not. And I think when you look at Christianity, what is so different than so many of the religions around the world? It's grace. Religion is man working their way to God, but Christianity is God coming down to us. And sometimes it's like, wait a second, he loves me so much that he's been pursuing me. That's what the God of the Bible does for us. Tim, how do you know? 38. If me and you die tomorrow and you had one more message to me with the younger generation, what would that be? And I would pray that you would use your life for something that really matters because when our life is over, are we going to be more focused about the inheritance or the legacy we left? Because inheritance is what you leave for someone, but I believe legacy is what you leave in someone. Tim, I'm proud of you man. Thank you man. I'm grateful that God uses screw-ups and so I'm not disqualified. I connect with everyone I interview. Could I get your contact? Yeah, of course. God bless you, dude.",
  "segments": [
    {
      "start": 0.0,
      "end": 3.3,
      "text": "Excuse me sir, how old were you when you became a millionaire?"
    },
    {
      "start": 3.6,
      "end": 4.7,
      "text": "Probably around 22."
    },
    {
      "start": 4.9,
      "end": 5.6,
      "text": "So you made it young."
    },
    {
      "start": 5.8,
      "end": 7.4,
      "text": "I was very fortunate and blessed."
    },
    {
      "start": 7.6,
      "end": 9.7,
      "text": "It won a lot of business for you it man, how did you get rich that early?"
    },
    {
      "start": 9.8,
      "end": 11.5,
      "text": "I was fortunate to be a quarterback in the NFL."
    },
    {
      "start": 11.7,
      "end": 12.2,
      "text": "So what's your name?"
    },
    {
      "start": 12.4,
      "end": 13.3,
      "text": "My name's Tim Tebow."
    },
    {
      "start": 13.5,
      "end": 15.7,
      "text": "Man I go all over the world interviewing millionaires and billionaires to help the"
    },
    {
      "start": 15.7,
      "end": 16.2,
      "text": "younger generation."
    },
    {
      "start": 16.4,
      "end": 17.5,
      "text": "Can I get a minute with you for the channel?"
    },
    {
      "start": 17.6,
      "end": 18.2,
      "text": "Yeah of course."
    },
    {
      "start": 18.4,
      "end": 20.7,
      "text": "What was the most amount of money that you made in a single year?"
    },
    {
      "start": 20.8,
      "end": 23.7,
      "text": "Somewhere between like 5 and 10 million or something I can't even remember, yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 23.8,
      "end": 26.4,
      "text": "What is the greatest piece of advice that you've received throughout your career?"
    },
    {
      "start": 26.4,
      "end": 31.6,
      "text": "The greatest form of tragedy is being successful at everything that doesn't matter."
    },
    {
      "start": 32.0,
      "end": 35.6,
      "text": "But we can take that success and we can use it for things that really matter."
    },
    {
      "start": 35.8,
      "end": 39.1,
      "text": "Now for the people watching, a lot of them know you as an NFL player, but after your"
    },
    {
      "start": 39.1,
      "end": 42.1,
      "text": "career you're doing something right now that nobody else is doing."
    },
    {
      "start": 42.4,
      "end": 43.2,
      "text": "What are you doing right now?"
    },
    {
      "start": 43.3,
      "end": 47.0,
      "text": "We're trying to fight back against the greatest evils in the world and that is human trafficking,"
    },
    {
      "start": 47.3,
      "end": 49.0,
      "text": "child exploitation, and child sacrifice."
    },
    {
      "start": 49.3,
      "end": 51.7,
      "text": "How crazy is that for people that don't understand the magnitude?"
    },
    {
      "start": 51.8,
      "end": 54.7,
      "text": "Today there's 50 plus million people that are being trafficked right now."
    },
    {
      "start": 54.8,
      "end": 55.5,
      "text": "People have no idea."
    },
    {
      "start": 55.5,
      "end": 56.1,
      "text": "We have no idea."
    },
    {
      "start": 56.3,
      "end": 61.0,
      "text": "We're truly so many times we really do have no idea, but we have to be able to spread that"
    },
    {
      "start": 61.0,
      "end": 63.7,
      "text": "awareness and it's taking place in every community in our country."
    },
    {
      "start": 63.9,
      "end": 64.5,
      "text": "Do you believe in God?"
    },
    {
      "start": 64.6,
      "end": 64.9,
      "text": "I do."
    },
    {
      "start": 65.1,
      "end": 65.6,
      "text": "Who is your God?"
    },
    {
      "start": 65.8,
      "end": 69.6,
      "text": "My God is the God of the Bible, God the Father, God the Son, and God the Holy Spirit."
    },
    {
      "start": 69.7,
      "end": 70.4,
      "text": "So you believe in Jesus?"
    },
    {
      "start": 70.7,
      "end": 70.9,
      "text": "I do."
    },
    {
      "start": 71.1,
      "end": 72.1,
      "text": "You're not afraid to say that either?"
    },
    {
      "start": 72.3,
      "end": 72.9,
      "text": "No I'm not."
    },
    {
      "start": 73.0,
      "end": 77.0,
      "text": "And I think when you look at Christianity, what is so different than so many of the"
    },
    {
      "start": 77.0,
      "end": 78.3,
      "text": "religions around the world?"
    },
    {
      "start": 78.6,
      "end": 79.1,
      "text": "It's grace."
    },
    {
      "start": 79.6,
      "end": 84.3,
      "text": "Religion is man working their way to God, but Christianity is God coming down to"
    },
    {
      "start": 84.3,
      "end": 84.6,
      "text": "us."
    },
    {
      "start": 84.6,
      "end": 88.6,
      "text": "And sometimes it's like, wait a second, he loves me so much that he's been pursuing me."
    },
    {
      "start": 88.8,
      "end": 90.7,
      "text": "That's what the God of the Bible does for us."
    },
    {
      "start": 90.9,
      "end": 91.5,
      "text": "Tim, how do you know?"
    },
    {
      "start": 91.7,
      "end": 92.0,
      "text": "38."
    },
    {
      "start": 92.3,
      "end": 95.5,
      "text": "If me and you die tomorrow and you had one more message to me with the younger generation,"
    },
    {
      "start": 95.6,
      "end": 96.2,
      "text": "what would that be?"
    },
    {
      "start": 96.3,
      "end": 100.6,
      "text": "And I would pray that you would use your life for something that really matters because"
    },
    {
      "start": 100.6,
      "end": 104.9,
      "text": "when our life is over, are we going to be more focused about the inheritance or the"
    },
    {
      "start": 104.9,
      "end": 105.8,
      "text": "legacy we left?"
    },
    {
      "start": 105.9,
      "end": 110.0,
      "text": "Because inheritance is what you leave for someone, but I believe legacy is what"
    },
    {
      "start": 110.0,
      "end": 111.1,
      "text": "you leave in someone."
    },
    {
      "start": 111.4,
      "end": 112.2,
      "text": "Tim, I'm proud of you man."
    },
    {
      "start": 112.4,
      "end": 112.9,
      "text": "Thank you man."
    },
    {
      "start": 112.9,
      "end": 115.9,
      "text": "I'm grateful that God uses screw-ups and so I'm not disqualified."
    },
    {
      "start": 116.2,
      "end": 117.2,
      "text": "I connect with everyone I interview."
    },
    {
      "start": 117.4,
      "end": 118.0,
      "text": "Could I get your contact?"
    },
    {
      "start": 118.1,
      "end": 118.5,
      "text": "Yeah, of course."
    },
    {
      "start": 118.7,
      "end": 119.3,
      "text": "God bless you, dude."
    }
  ],
